Package core

Class By

java.lang.Object
core.By
public class By extends Object
This class consists of element finding logic methods. It provides various methods to find elements based on different attributes and criteria. It also supports image-based and OCR-based element searches. Note: The methods in this class use the `Driver` class for element search and automation. Make sure to initialize the `Driver` before using any of the methods.
Author:
Dhanush

    • findElementsByText

      public static List<mmarquee.automation.Element> findElementsByText​(mmarquee.automation.ControlType controlType, String value, core.By.FindOption findOption) throws mmarquee.automation.AutomationException
      Finds elements with a specific help text attribute and control type.
      Parameters:
      controlType - The type of the control to search for (e.g., Button, TextBox, etc.).
      value - The help text attribute value to match elements against.
      findOption - An enumeration specifying whether to find the FIRST matching element or ALL matching elements.
      Returns:
      A list of elements that match the specified help text and control type based on the chosen find option.
      Throws:
      mmarquee.automation.AutomationException - If there is an error during the automation process.
      IllegalArgumentException - If any of the input parameters (controlType, value, or findOption) are invalid.

    • findImageInImage

      public static SikuliElement findImageInImage​(String searchImage, String findImage) throws CustomImageSearchException
      Finds an element with the specified image inside another image or screen.
      Parameters:
      searchImage - The filename of the image where the search for the findImage should happen. Use "SCREEN" to search on the entire screen.
      findImage - The filename of the image to find inside the searchImage.
      Returns:
      A SikuliElement representing the found region.
      Throws:
      CustomImageSearchException - If the image search fails or the image filenames are null or empty.

    • findTextUsingOCR

      public static SikuliElement findTextUsingOCR​(String searchImage, String text) throws CustomOCRFailedException
      Finds an element containing the specified text using OCR inside an image or screen.
      Parameters:
      searchImage - The filename of the image where the OCR search for the text should happen. Use "SCREEN" to search on the entire screen.
      text - The text to find using OCR.
      Returns:
      A SikuliElement representing the found region containing the text.
      Throws:
      CustomOCRFailedException - If the OCR search fails or the image filename or text is null or empty.

    • createSikuliElementAtLocation

      public static SikuliElement createSikuliElementAtLocation​(int screenX, int screenY) throws CustomLocationException
      Creates a SikuliElement at the specified (x, y) coordinates on the screen.
      Parameters:
      screenX - The x-coordinate of the location to create the SikuliElement.
      screenY - The y-coordinate of the location to create the SikuliElement.
      Returns:
      A SikuliElement representing the region at the specified coordinates.
      Throws:
      CustomLocationException - If the (x, y) coordinates are not valid screen coordinates.
